00:53:40.540 --> 00:53:43.120
is still going to be
true going forward,

00:53:43.120 --> 00:53:45.490
in the face of all of
these scientists telling us

00:53:45.490 --> 00:53:49.360
that they're creating a great
deal of harmful side effects

00:53:49.360 --> 00:53:51.620
that we haven't
really felt much yet,

00:53:51.620 --> 00:53:53.240
but we will feel in the future?

00:53:56.530 --> 00:53:59.440
ALEX EPSTEIN: Really
important issue, generally,

00:53:59.440 --> 00:54:01.010
of how do we--

00:54:01.010 --> 00:54:04.750
what is the relationship
between expert claims

00:54:04.750 --> 00:54:06.920
and our own thinking?

00:54:06.920 --> 00:54:09.340
And I think the
two prevalent ways

00:54:09.340 --> 00:54:10.640
of dealing with this are wrong.

00:54:10.640 --> 00:54:15.730
So one is just defer to
experts or even bow to experts

00:54:15.730 --> 00:54:18.400
or meet what media tells
us experts, so the people

00:54:18.400 --> 00:54:20.770
who say, well, if
97% of scientists

00:54:20.770 --> 00:54:23.905
agree, who am I
to question that?

00:54:23.905 --> 00:54:25.030
So that's one kind of view.

00:54:25.030 --> 00:54:27.859
And the other is that
consensus doesn't matter,

00:54:27.859 --> 00:54:28.900
experts are always wrong.

00:54:28.900 --> 00:54:29.650
And that sort of--

00:54:29.650 --> 00:54:31.540
I think those are
both obviously wrong.

00:54:31.540 --> 00:54:34.270
So you need experts,
but historically, we

00:54:34.270 --> 00:54:38.170
know that experts are
extremely, extremely fallible

00:54:38.170 --> 00:54:41.850
and are often used
in very bad ways.

00:54:41.850 --> 00:54:44.320
In the field of
nutrition, for example,

00:54:44.320 --> 00:54:46.450
let's say, the government
sponsored Food Pyramid

00:54:46.450 --> 00:54:49.720
as a universal guide to food,
almost everyone agrees, OK,

00:54:49.720 --> 00:54:50.750
that was wrong.

00:54:50.750 --> 00:54:53.040
But at the time, if you go
back, now, we could say,

00:54:53.040 --> 00:54:54.623
oh, they were wrong
but we were right.

00:54:54.623 --> 00:54:56.920
But but we were them once.

00:54:56.920 --> 00:55:00.290
And in maybe one of
the worst examples

00:55:00.290 --> 00:55:06.550
is in the field of genetics,
people conflating evolution

00:55:06.550 --> 00:55:08.920
with eugenics and having
many leading thinkers

00:55:08.920 --> 00:55:11.470
and scientists in society
being in favor of things

00:55:11.470 --> 00:55:14.330
like forced sterilization
and different forms of racism

00:55:14.330 --> 00:55:14.830
and whatnot.

00:55:17.740 --> 00:55:20.410
And that was put forward
as the experts tell us.

00:55:20.410 --> 00:55:24.640
It was, I call it not global
warming but global dumbing.

00:55:24.640 --> 00:55:27.010
That was the theory, that,
oh, if you allow people

00:55:27.010 --> 00:55:29.382
to procreate without
sterilization,

00:55:29.382 --> 00:55:31.840
then all the dumb people are
going to sleep with each other

00:55:31.840 --> 00:55:33.530
and we're going to
have too dumb people.

00:55:33.530 --> 00:55:36.040
And so we need to clamp
down and the science

00:55:36.040 --> 00:55:38.350
says this is what we do.

00:55:38.350 --> 00:55:41.515
What we really need to do is
we need the proper relationship

00:55:41.515 --> 00:55:46.900
with experts, which, one basic
thing is that I describe it

00:55:46.900 --> 00:55:52.450
in the book as they should
function as advisers, not

00:55:52.450 --> 00:55:53.280
authorities.

00:55:53.280 --> 00:55:55.440
So an authority is
somebody you bow to.

00:55:55.440 --> 00:55:57.820
It has a religious connotation.

00:55:57.820 --> 00:56:02.770
An advisor is somebody who has
much more context in a given

00:56:02.770 --> 00:56:05.320
field but who gives you an
explanation, who gives you

00:56:05.320 --> 00:56:07.810
a very clear explanation
of what he knows,

00:56:07.810 --> 00:56:10.120
what he doesn't know,
what he sort of knows,

00:56:10.120 --> 00:56:12.760
what the strength
of evidence is.

00:56:12.760 --> 00:56:15.520
And that's what we really
need from the field of climate

00:56:15.520 --> 00:56:16.720
science.

00:56:16.720 --> 00:56:19.840
And unfortunately, we have
not gotten that whatsoever

00:56:19.840 --> 00:56:21.340
for various structural reasons.

00:56:21.340 --> 00:56:23.800
But whatever the reasons
are, we have not gotten that.

00:56:23.800 --> 00:56:27.640
And the whole sloppiness
issue is a huge part of it.

00:56:27.640 --> 00:56:29.650
We just have all these--
the public agencies say

00:56:29.650 --> 00:56:34.490
97% of scientists agree that,
then it's not really clear,

00:56:34.490 --> 00:56:38.290
and then you look into it
and it's, oh, it's actually

00:56:38.290 --> 00:56:41.350
that of the mild amount
of warming that we've had,

00:56:41.350 --> 00:56:42.792
we caused over 50%.

00:56:42.792 --> 00:56:44.750
And then you see, well,
how can you prove that?

00:56:44.750 --> 00:56:46.930
And they have no
mechanism of proving that.

00:56:46.930 --> 00:56:49.180
And then you look into
97%, and then it's

00:56:49.180 --> 00:56:51.020
actually not anywhere near 97%.

00:56:51.020 --> 00:56:53.620
This is-- there's a
97% section in the book

00:56:53.620 --> 00:56:55.630
about the actual data here.

00:56:55.630 --> 00:57:00.220
So this is a field
where the actual state

00:57:00.220 --> 00:57:05.430
of knowledge in the field is
systematically mis-reported.

00:57:05.430 --> 00:57:07.830
And that's one thing.

00:57:07.830 --> 00:57:09.675
And then another thing
is, so how accurately

00:57:09.675 --> 00:57:12.420
is it reporting things badly?

00:57:12.420 --> 00:57:15.510
And then the other thing
is, how much do they know?

00:57:15.510 --> 00:57:17.910
So one question is how
much-- every field has

00:57:17.910 --> 00:57:19.990
a different degree of maturity.

00:57:19.990 --> 00:57:23.740
So physicists applying
laws of mechanics,

00:57:23.740 --> 00:57:28.770
or, let's say, applying
quantum electrodynamics have

00:57:28.770 --> 00:57:31.200
huge amounts of
precision at making

00:57:31.200 --> 00:57:33.060
lots and lots of predictions.

00:57:33.060 --> 00:57:37.590
Climate modelers have
no success whatsoever.

00:57:37.590 --> 00:57:40.940
That's not to demean
them as human beings.

00:57:40.940 --> 00:57:44.610
It's just they're not there,
just like economic modelers,

00:57:44.610 --> 00:57:46.800
generally, have
very poor records.

00:57:46.800 --> 00:57:49.120
So we need this
objectivity from fields

00:57:49.120 --> 00:57:51.360
to know how developed
a field is this,

00:57:51.360 --> 00:57:54.370
and what is the best of
what they can tell us?

00:57:54.370 --> 00:57:57.457
And so when you hear
when they don't do that,

00:57:57.457 --> 00:57:59.040
it's very, very hard
to operate, which

00:57:59.040 --> 00:58:00.510
is why I spent a lot of time--

00:58:00.510 --> 00:58:02.760
so you're basically saying,
well, all these scientists

00:58:02.760 --> 00:58:03.454
say this.

00:58:03.454 --> 00:58:04.620
How can you say differently?

00:58:04.620 --> 00:58:06.230
And I'm saying, well,
I looked into it,

00:58:06.230 --> 00:58:08.521
and I don't think that they
say that, and to the extent

00:58:08.521 --> 00:58:11.230
they say that, they
can't prove that.

00:58:11.230 --> 00:58:14.560
So I think people need to
look into it for themselves.

00:58:14.560 --> 00:58:17.640
But one giveaway
in your question

00:58:17.640 --> 00:58:20.650
is that these scientists
say that it's harmful.

00:58:20.650 --> 00:58:21.960
So harmful is an--

00:58:21.960 --> 00:58:24.420
harmful of any
environmental factor

00:58:24.420 --> 00:58:26.790
is always going to be a
combination of environment

00:58:26.790 --> 00:58:28.300
and technology, right?

00:58:28.300 --> 00:58:31.560
So a harmful storm
200 years ago could

